Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Joseph Christian Blanco in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense requested a final pre-trial and jury trial date. Defendant Joseph Christian Blanco in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. New defense counsel requests an adjournment.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 23. Parties are advised that as of August 1, 2015, this case is assigned to br. 23, Judge Grady in room 515 of the courthouse.  Status conference scheduled for August 24, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with J.D.

Court conducted Indigency Hearing. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by court. Court held colloquy with defendant. Defendant requested court appointed counsel and agreed to reimburse Milwaukee County for the expense. The court appointed Atty. Joel Rosenthal, present in court via telephone, to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $60.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning the 1st of the month after the completion of the case, and then the 1st of each month there after. Court advised defendant failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Signed, Distributed & Filed, Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense. Case is adjourned for a Status of Counsel date in branch 45.

Defendant Joseph Christian Blanco in court.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Amended Complaint filed by state adding Count 2:  Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.19(1), 939.51(3), a Class A Misdemeanor.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Copy of Complaint given to defendant. Defendant waived the reading of the complaint.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of defendant.  Status conference scheduled for July 31, 2015 at 08:30 am.
The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for 07-13-2015 at 08:30 am.
